The stuff she was taught was realistic and made it so she didn't have to 'live like a rabbit' and could still do things she enjoys. Made huge improvements to her diabetes and her weight. The folks who run the class were really happy and willing to adapt things to her blindness, describe things and make her feel welcome. Made friendships. Can take it again to refresh. The classes are optimistic, 'there are solutions to these problems, you just have to find the one that works for you, or that you can work with.' Getting a handle on what she's eating and why she's eating it, realizing she can still have things she enjoys, just moderately.    Liked that it was online, because it was more accessible for her because she just needs someone to help her set it up, instead of take her to and from a physical location.
